        <div id="what is reproduction" class="content">
 <h3>What Is Reproduction?</h3></div>
Reproduction can be defined as the ability and capability of living things to give birth to there young ones or to reproduce to there look alikes.<br>
<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Reproduction#:~:text=Reproduction%20or%20procreation,two%20parental%20organisms.">Learn More On Reproduction.</a><br>
<br>Reproduction can be divided into two parts:<br>
<strong>sexual</strong> And <strong>Asexual</strong> Reproduction <br>
</div>
<div id="what is sexual reproduction">
    <h3>What Is Sexual Reproduction</h3>
Sexual Reproduction can be defined as when both
 parents comes together in other to produce a younger
  one i.e <em class="text"> The fussion of the male and female gamet to produce a zygote or  (zygospore in plants).</em><br>


<div id="what is asexual reproduction" class="content">
<h3>    What Is Asexual Reproduction?</h3>
</div>
<p>Asexual Reproduction can be defined as a type of reproduction that involes only one parent
i.e <em>
    it produce it young one singly without any other parent .</em><br></p>
        <h3>Types Of Asexual Reproduction<br></h3>
    </h3>
    There are different types of Asexual Reproduction the are :<br>
    <ul>
        <li>Binary fussion</li>
        <li>Conjugation</li>
        <li>Grafting</li>
        <li>Budding</li>
        <li>Marcoting <strong>etc</strong></li>
    </ul>
    <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Asexual_reproduction#:~:text=with%20budding.-,Vegetative%20propagation%5Bedit%5D,Sex,-References%5Bedit" target="_blank">Learn More</a>
